WEBVTT

00:07.507 --> 00:10.642
Tom Sullivan was family to me,

00:10.644 --> 00:12.444
to us.

00:12.446 --> 00:14.346
I grew up
being rocked on his knee,

00:14.348 --> 00:16.749
sitting in front of him
on his horse.

00:16.751 --> 00:18.617
And daddy was gone
most of the time,

00:18.619 --> 00:21.153
so it was tom who taught
my brothers and... and me

00:21.155 --> 00:24.123
how to ride and shoot.

00:24.125 --> 00:25.724
And I can't think
of a single good time

00:25.726 --> 00:29.294
I ever had on this ranch
that didn't involve that man.

00:29.296 --> 00:32.264
I mean, he was there when...
When Sally and I got married...

00:32.266 --> 00:34.400
Amen.

00:34.402 --> 00:36.802
Was there when the kids
were born.

00:36.804 --> 00:41.407
I watched you guys grow up
on his knee just like I did.

00:41.409 --> 00:43.308
He was there
for all the bad times as well.

00:43.310 --> 00:44.510
Yes, he was.

00:44.512 --> 00:47.579
He was there that day

00:47.581 --> 00:50.749
the apache killed my...
My mother and my brother.

00:50.751 --> 00:55.054
He was the reason
Phineas and I survived.

00:55.056 --> 00:57.089
He fought like a mother bear
to protect us.

00:57.091 --> 00:59.224
Quite a soldier.

00:59.226 --> 01:00.692
He saved us...

01:00.694 --> 01:02.795
Nobody better.

01:02.797 --> 01:04.696
And I couldn't save him.

01:04.697 --> 01:09.668
And some of you might say to me,
"well, Peter, he forgives you."

01:09.670 --> 01:11.403
Right now he's living in a place

01:11.405 --> 01:14.106
where the streams run clear...

01:14.108 --> 01:15.574
and the grass is up
to your chest,

01:15.576 --> 01:18.677
- the horses never get tired.
- That's right.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.447
That's right.

01:21.449 --> 01:23.816
I don't know
if any of that is real.

01:25.718 --> 01:28.587
I used to think someone was
watching over us,

01:28.589 --> 01:30.556
but these days,
when I look around,

01:30.558 --> 01:32.724
I'm not sure about that.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.131
I'm finished.

01:40.834 --> 01:44.236
Please, carry on, brother.

01:44.238 --> 01:46.138
Of course. Can I go, too?

01:46.140 --> 01:48.107
No, you give me a moment
with your daddy.

01:48.109 --> 01:49.708
There's a good girl.

01:49.710 --> 01:51.477
<i>A reading from revelation.</i>

01:51.479 --> 01:53.779
"And I heard a voice
from heaven saying,"

01:53.781 --> 01:55.614
blessed are the dead

01:55.616 --> 01:57.883
"who die in the lord
from now on."

01:57.885 --> 02:00.519
Perhaps you should go away
for a spell.

02:00.521 --> 02:02.554
Go up to Austin, see your wife.

02:02.556 --> 02:04.756
I don't think
that's a good idea.

02:04.758 --> 02:08.293
I'm not a source of comfort
for her.

02:08.294 --> 02:10.795
It ain't her I'm worried about.

02:10.798 --> 02:13.699
Your children need a daddy.

02:13.701 --> 02:16.635
This ranch needs a leader.

02:16.637 --> 02:20.672
So whatever it takes
to get your head right,

02:20.674 --> 02:23.842
you better do it.

02:23.844 --> 02:27.513
Yes, sir. Whatever you say, sir.

